{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large serving bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in couscous. Pour over boiling water (refer to packet instructions for amount). Cover with cling film and set aside for 5 minutes, or until fluffy and all water has been absorbed.","Meanwhile, place ginger and onion in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add carrots and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add raisins, cashew nuts, chickpeas and curry powder then mix <nobr>15 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Fluff up couscous with a fork to separate grains then stir salad mix into couscous. Garnish with coriander before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["225 g couscous","water, boiling, according to packet instructions","10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","30 g red onion, quartered","120 g carrots, cut in pieces","25 g raisins","25 g cashew nuts (unsalted, unroasted)","1 tin cooked chickpeas, 1 x 400 g tin (drained weight approx. 240 g)","1 Tbsp curry powder, or to taste","1 Tbsp fresh coriander leaves, roughly chopped, for garnish"]}],"id":"r97064","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-G7B9miG3qi0\/XZVRu7JS5iI\/AAAAAAAAdSQ\/0uBc7HhCLNc94VLwtQ3p0ntTTZEH2-a4wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_vGE0ETOBDFa1GjRF.png","title":"Curried Couscous, Carrot and Chickpea Salad","publishedAt":"2016-05-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.7 g","fat":"4.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"40 g","calories":"976 kJ \/ 233 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large serving bowl, cling film","hintsAndTricks":["Try adding diced or crumbled feta cheese before serving.","Substitute carrots with an equal weight of florets from a small head of broccoli."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","10m","6 portions"]}